translated: Ekdahl, Agne Algot William, parish priest, Olofström, born on 27/12/00 in Ö. Vemjmieirföv, Kristianstad county, son of the piano factory worker Joh. E. and Kristina Månsson. Married in 1934 to Karin Norberg. They have one child: Birgitta, born in 1935. He studied at Lund's private elementary school in 1921 and earned a Bachelor's degree in 1925 and a Master's degree in theology from Lund University in 1928. He passed his practical theology exam and was ordained a priest in Lund's diocese in 1929. He was a vicar in Silvåkra and Revinge from 1929 to 1930, and an ordained parish priest in Jämshög parish since 1930. He is a member of Jämshög's church council, chairman of Olofström's children's association, a member and vice chairman of Olofström's primary school board, and chairman of the board of Olofström's high school.
